@title Forward Factory contract
 @notice This contract allows users to create a new (Forward contract) position into the Aave protocol

@title Forward Factory contract
 @notice This contract allows users to create a new (Forward contract) position into the Aave protocol

createForward(uint256,string,uint256,str.details: Owner deposits token into aaveLendingPoolCore by calling deposit function

params._exchangeRate: fixed amount of ETH or ERC20 to be received upon settlement date
params._exchangeToken: symbol of the token to match the position
params._executingTime: When the position reaches settlement date
params._expirationTime: time in minutes, hours or days that the position will be opened to be matched
params._value: Value of the position in Eth or ERC20

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner.     * NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

createForward(uint256,string,uint256,str.notice: ///////////////////////////////// ///// POSITION SETUP //////////// /////////////////////////////////This contract is the foundation for any created Forward contract

userdoc.notice: This contract allows users to create a new (Forward contract) position into the Aave protocol
